arXiv.abstract:
We study the moduli space of handlebodies diffeomorphic to $(D^{n+1}	imes S^{n})^{
atural g}$, i.e. the classifying space $BDiff((D^{n+1}	imes S^n)^{
atural g}, D^{2n})$ of the group of diffeomorphisms that restrict to the identity near a $2n$-dimensional disk embedded in the boundary, $\partial(D^{n+1}	imes S^n)^{
atural g}$. We construct a map $colim_{g	o\infty}BDiff((D^{n+1}	imes S^n)^{
atural g}, D^{2n}) \longrightarrow Q_{0}BO(2n+1)\langle n angle_{+}$ and prove that it induces an isomorphism on integral homology in the case that $2n+1 \geq 9$. Above, $BO(2n+1)\langle n angle$ denotes the $n$-connective cover of $BO(2n+1)$. The (co)homology of the space $Q_{0}BO(2n+1)\langle n angle_{+}$ is well understood and so our results enable one to compute the homology groups $H_{k}(BDiff((D^{n+1}	imes S^n)^{
atural g}, D^{2n}))$ in a range of degrees when $k << g$. Our main theorem can be viewed as an analogue of the Madsen-Weiss theorem for the moduli spaces of surfaces and the recent theorem of Galatius and Randal-Williams for the moduli spaces of manifolds of dimension $2n \geq 6$.
